# The credentials files are committed for CI/CD as baseline/templates
# that are "stale" tokens that get auto-regenerated when tests are
# run.  These are test-only credentials for a dev POD server, not
# production.

# Because the files are already in the repo we need to tell our
# particular clone of the repository (i.e., for each developer) to
# assume the files are unchanged, since they will be updated for each
# test run.

# git update-index --assume-unchanged integration_test/fixtures/auth_tokens.json
# git update-index --assume-unchanged integration_test/fixtures/complete_auth_data.json

# To undo this:

# git update-index --no-assume-unchanged integration_test/fixtures/auth_tokens.json
# git update-index --no-assume-unchanged integration_test/fixtures/complete_auth_data.json

# To see which files are marked this way:

# git ls-files -v | grep '^h'

# Integration test auth data (contains sensitive tokens)

# fixtures/auth_tokens.json
# fixtures/complete_auth_data.json
# fixtures/test_credentials.json

# Integration test TMDB API key (contains sensitive API key)

fixtures/tmdb_api_key.json
